      <span class="warn-box-ico">&#9888;</span>
      <p><strong>The #1 reason ashwagandha gummies "don't work" for some people is under-dosing.</strong> If your gummy contains less than 300mg of a standardized extract (KSM-66 or Sensoril), you are not taking enough to replicate clinical trial results. Before concluding that ashwagandha does not work for you, verify that your product delivers an adequate dose. Check our <a href="/best-ashwagandha-gummies/">best ashwagandha gummies</a> guide for products with verified clinical-dose formulations.</p>
